reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I’m been on the search for deodorant that prevents smell. I am not focused the sweating because I luv win Texas and the summer time is pretty steamy. Sweating is natural so that wasn’t my focus on my quest for deodorant. It the was smell. My armpits would stink so bad and become so musky. I do not use Duradry by itself. What I have found that works is immediately after my shower I use a roll on deodorant, specifically Mitchum. I roll it right into my armpits, all over. It takes about 5-10 minutes to fully dry. Once it’s dried, I apply Duradry right over. I’ve been doing this for a month and the results have been 180 degrees for the better. Not only have I fixed the musky smell but the wet sweatiness is also no longer there. I’ve haven’t tried Duradry alone but I have used other deodorants for the second application and the results were no where near what I get when I combine Mitchum and Duradry. Definitely worth the shot if you are a heavy sweater kind of person. The smell of the deodorant is mid. I got the Endgame scent and it’s okay. Nothing fantastic about the smell but it also doesn’t smell terribly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I have tried EVERYTHING & this is the only deodorant I have found that ACTUALLY WORKS & so far hasn't stopped working!I usually have to change my deodorant every few months because my body become immune to it. So far this has been amazing & keeps me smelling fresh.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars It’s works for a while
reviews.reviewText: That being said, I love the smell and the feeling. It also didn’t irritate my underarms after waxing. If i do wax, I do it at night before bed and apply the deodorant in the morning so I’m assuming that’s why it doesn’t irritate the skin. After a while, I noticed it stopped working for my underarms. I sweat like a mf especially when my anxiety spikes and it really helped in the beginning but now not so much. So I may need to explore deodorants again but it is good.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I found out about this product while my son was doing a clinical trial for it and I must say compared to other brands and I have tried a ton it works very well. I only sweat through if I take my herbal supplements that have thermogenic products in them so it's to be expected. I do suggest getting the wash as well because whatever is in this makes a film over your sink that is sticky to touch if you try to wipe off and it's meant to be resistant. It can clog pores if you don't remove it thoughly periodically.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Quality of product doesn't match the price...
reviews.reviewText: The stick itself stopped working halfway through. I had to make it go up and down, up and down and then I could get more product. When I got down to the bottom there's air pockets in it. It doesn't seem to be a solid pour and I've never had that happen even in cheap solids. Not bad, but for the price you'd expect to have a good solid product that I'd want to set on auto-ship. No go.

reviews.reviewText: After trying countless brands, I finally found one that works. Keeps your pits dry, odor eliminated and embarrassment non existent.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Didn’t work for me
reviews.reviewText: I was so excited to try this, I did only buy the deodorant instead of the whole 3 system. After using natural deodorants for almost a decade, I decided to go back to using an antiperspirant deodorant to help with the sweating aspect, and still wanted a product that was clean. Sadly this has not worked for me with sweating and I smell horrible. I haven’t even smelled this poorly with the natural deo’s.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works great for smell, leaves residue
reviews.reviewText: I love this deodorant as this along with the wash and PM antiperspirant work wonders! But my bras and the inside of my shirts are literally stained from this product. It’s unfortunate because this is the only deodorant I have found that works long term. I REALLY HOPE DURADRY MAKES A TRANSPARENT GEL FORMULA!! This would fix any issues I have with the product.

After using this for about 4-5 days (once a day only), I started feeling progressively more itchiness in my armpits (not too extreme, but definitely not vibing with the product). I stopped using it.On the 2nd day after I stopped using it, I woke up with intense itching around the armpits and that's when I noticed a rash had appeared (last 2 photos were on the evening of 1st day). The next morning (today - first 3 pictures), if anything, it seems even worse. I'm thinking I might need to seek medical guidance) .I'm just happy I didn't invest in the whole kit.It might work for some people (I saw positive reviews before buying it) but use it with caution..
